Steps.Message: Update at 14:57 - This is Rob from the messaging team at UK Power Networks; I've taken over from James and I'll be keeping you updated with progress as our staff continue works to get your power back on this afternoon. Further specialist lines teams and field engineers are now in the area and are working to repair and re-erect our fallen overhead cabling. This can take some time due to the logistics and equipment involved, but we're still hoping to have all the power restored by 18:30-19:30. I know it's difficult being without power in the cold, but I'll continue to keep you updated, and if you need any further support our team are always here on 08003163105.

We became aware of this power cut at 12:07. We’re sorry for any disruption this may have caused you. We didn’t know in advance there would be a power cut, but now that we know, our teams will do everything they can to get your power back quickly. Engineers in our control room have switched some customers power back on in your area. To get everyone’s power back on we may need to attend to investigate and make repairs. We’ll continue to update you until everyone’s power is back on.
Steps.Name: We are restoring customers automatically

Steps.Message: We have engineers on their way. As this is affecting your area, they will not need to attend your property. Rest assured once they arrive, they’ll work as quickly as is safely possible to get your power back on.
Steps.Name: Engineers on their way

Steps.Message: Engineers are now on site, carrying out investigations into the fault. Once they have completed their assessment, they will carry out repairs.
Steps.Name: Engineers investigating and fixing
